Hi everyone, I am going to be speaking about NEAT software at an 
interesti=
ng workshop at GECCO 2007 called the "2007 GECCO Workshop on 
Open-Source S=
oftware for Applied Genetic and Evolutionary Computation":

Here's the webs=
ite for the workshop:

http://www.epistasis.org/softgec2007.html

This work=
shop is a unique opportunity to highlight what's been going 
on with NEAT a=
s a software platform as opposed to talking about the 
academic research si=
de of it (which is usually all I have a chance to 
do).  

I think somethin=
g pretty unique and special has happened in this 
community that I've never=
 really seen elsewhere in the Evolutionary 
Computation world, which is bas=
ically a decentralized proliferation of 
NEAT platforms and spinoffs.  I th=
ink it will be very interesting for 
people to see how this community has s=
upported its software and each 
other through this decentralized approach. =
 

In that spirit I plan to highlight all the existing public releases to 
=
give people a sense of the breadth of what's available.  

Therefore, if yo=
u have a public NEAT version (or spinoff project such 
as genetic art) that=
 you believe I don't know about and would like 
mentioned, please feel free=
 to let me know and I will mention your 
work as well.  

Please note that =
private projects can't be included because after all 
the workshop is about=
 "open source" software.

I'm looking forward to letting people know about =
all the great work a 
lot of you have done!

thanks,

ken
